💯 agree. When I filled in Stolis, I was “ha ha yeah” as in hesitant agreement (ref. Recent Kuggelman puzzle). But then Pepsis? And Dews? (Didn’t have to be clued referencing “some yellow-green sodas”). Felt kinda like the puzzle could have been titled “Brought to you by….”
Oreo, Ragu, and Edys failed to make the cut (this time).

@Charles Peterson
What is "ugh" about STOLIS? First, the brand is Latvian, not Russian. Second, there are multiple varieties of the brand (orange, cranberry, raspberry, etc) so there's nothing suss about the plural. I prefer Tito's myself, but it's a premium vodka, and a proper alternative to Absolut, as clued.

Stoli, darling!

